    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Frederick B. Serger   (1889-1965) was an American painter known for his  floral still lifes and landscapes.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Frederick B. Serger Papers</emph> consists of correspondence, writings, exhibition catalogues and clippings.  The bulk of the collection is exhibit catalogs.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>The entire collection is arranged roughly chronologically.</p>
    </arrangement>
